A 30-year-old woman, known only as Hollie, said she thought her life was over when she was diagnosed with relapsing-remitting multiple sclerosis in September 2013 .
The Sydney celebrity chef shared a testimonial with his 868,000-plus followers on Facebook on Saturday .
'Having MS means I'm always sapped of energy, have numbness, pins and needles, pain, poor concentration, etc. Not any more!' she wrote .
Pete Evans shared a similar testimonial on social media on Saturday, claiming that the modern Australian diet is behind the rise in autism .